om Aboriginal ‘songlines’ to modern-day road trips. It also tells the stories of iconic roads, including the Birdsville Track, Stuart Highway and Great Ocean Road, and suggests alternative approaches to heritage and tourism interpretation of these important routes. The ongoing impact of the colonial past on Indigenous peoples and contemporary Australian society and culture – including representations of the road and road travel – is explored throughout the book. The volume offers a new way of thinking about roads and road tourism as important strands in a nation’s cultural fabric.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aAutomobile travelxSocial aspectszAustralia. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszAustralia. 4aAustralasian & Pacific history. 4aSocial & cultural history. 4aTourism industry. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aCultural Routes.  aRoad literature.  aRoad movies.  aRoad tourism.  aRoads .  aThe road.  acultural heritage.  acultural history.  aroad heritage .  aroad history.  aroad trip.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCVP eBook-Package Contemporary 2016-2020z978311075434640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184541669040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845416690423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781845416690/original  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK